Nume Ekeghe Nteje, in Oyi local government area of Anambra state, witnessed as over 500 members of the Omambala Progressive Forum, came endorsed their senatorial district, Senator Stella Oduah for another term The Omambala Progressive Forum consisting of members drawn from the four(4) LGA’s that make up the Omambala region; Anambra East, Anambra West, Oyi, and Ayamelum, had their first meeting of the year and they as usual brought up the various issues affecting their region amongst which was the forthcoming National Assembly elections in 2023. A statement by Stella Oduah’s media team, stated that the meeting had several speakers stressing on the need for sustained quality representation at the National Assembly with members expressing gratitude and appreciation to the incumbent lawmaker representing their senatorial district, Senator Stella Oduah, whom they described as heaven sent and the people’s choice for the forthcoming elections. Speaker after speaker, highlighted the noble and commendable attributes of the distinguished senator whilst unanimously affirming that she had done more than all the past occupants of the office put together. They then pleaded and asked that she run for another term since it was clear that she had the interest of the people at heart and stressed that her tenures had ushered in tangible results, unprecedented growth and development in the region. They applauded her different laudable projects and initiatives such as the agricultural loans, the Covid-19 survival fund, the building of roads, ICT centers, school blocks, water boreholes, the uncountable empowerment schemes and the human capital development training programs. After much deliberation and consultation, the forum issued a communique jointly signed by key stakeholders of the forum amongst whom were; Mr Emeka Small Nzekwe- Anambra east LGA (DG SSO POLITICAL MOVEMENT), Mr Amaechi Chimeze- Oyi LGA, Chief Alex Okonkwo- Anambra west LGA, John Onyimonyi- Ayamelum LGA, Mrs Angela Ejike- Ayamelum LGA and Barr Chucks Nnalue- Ayamelum LGA. Jideofor Okuzua- Oyi LGA, Chief Emma Onyimeyi- Anambra west LGA, Augustine Chuweike Egwu- Anambra east LGA, Mrs Linda Malubeze- Anambra east LGA and Barr Kingsley Nwakobu- Ayamelum LGA. Regina Nwagbogu- Anambra east LGA, Mrs Ogo Nwasi- anambra east LGA and Mrs Ujue Osakwe- Anambra east LGA They unanimously endorsed the distinguished Senator Stella Oduah as their preferred candidate for the next elections. This is the first major endorsement the senator is receiving this year and it goes a long way to show how connected she is to the grassroots level.